{"type":"message","id":"fbc07a98","parentId":"1ee7c564","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:01:20.133Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me commit these changes.","thinkingSignature":"f6028a5f05104d9884101ed5508856f3633de36581017a1b9d7b88623280e6ac"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ayt6q1nfqd7c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && git commit -m \"audit fixes: pct_change NaN, vectorized CSV, order execution simulator\n\n1. risk/exit_engine.py: pct_change() now returns NaN instead of 0.0\n   for invalid inputs (zero/negative prices) - avoids silent failures\n   on suspended stocks\n\n2. risk/exit_engine.py: load_price_snapshot() and load_latest_ma_snapshot()\n   replaced row-by-row itertuples loops with pandas vectorized\n   groupby/agg operations - chunksize increased 200k->500k\n\n3. execution/simulator.py: new order execution simulator implementing:\n   - Limit-up day: BUY orders rejected\n   - Limit-down day: SELL orders rejected\n   - Partial fills for oversized orders (> ADV20 threshold)\n   - T+1 restriction tracking\n   - Configurable slippage (8bps buy / 5bps sell)\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed","usage":{"input":66557,"output":237,"cacheRead":19971,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86765,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775577674544,"responseId":"06245d4bbb2aadb8c2e28bc68426cdbf"}}
