{"type":"message","id":"cc48259a","parentId":"a9fe803b","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:12:46.908Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me handle item 8: 涨跌停判断优化. The issue is in `run_backtest.py` where the limit up/down detection uses `close[0]` instead of `high[0]/low[0]`.","thinkingSignature":"6ea4411a1e3fa4e782f312efde41fe6efe77feacd6f1d28016775f6bb5a1f6df"},{"type":"text","text":"Now fix item 8 — 涨跌停判断优化 in `run_backtest.py`:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_idkkcf35suy5_1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":25,"offset":48,"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/backtest/run_backtest.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed","usage":{"input":89345,"output":137,"cacheRead":19971,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109453,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775578363678,"responseId":"06245ffb77600285ccca424e58a8e7b9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2d92e9e7","parentId":"cc48259a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:12:46.979Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_idkkcf35suy5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"            \"sell_suspended\": 0,\n            \"sell_limit_down\": 0,\n            \"sell_t_plus_1\": 0,\n            \"insufficient_lot\": 0,\n        }\n\n    def _is_suspended(self):\n        return int(self.data.suspended[0]) == 1\n\n    def _is_limit_up(self):\n        return float(self.data.close[0]) >= float(self.data.limit_up[0]) - 1e-8\n\n    def _is_limit_down(self):\n        return float(self.data.close[0]) <= float(self.data.limit_down[0]) + 1e-8\n\n    def _calc_buy_size(self):\n        price = float(self.data.close[0])\n        if price <= 0:\n            return 0\n        cash_budget = self.broker.getcash() * self.p.stake_cash_ratio\n        risk_budget = self.broker.getvalue() * self.p.max_single_position\n        budget = min(cash_budget, risk_budget)\n        raw_size = int(budget / price)\n        return (raw_size // self.p.lot_size) * self.p.lot_size\n\n\n[146 more lines in file. Use offset=73 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775578366974}}
{"type":"message","id":"482c9bef","parentId":"2d92e9e7","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:12:56.768Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. The `_is_limit_up()` and `_is_limit_down()` methods use `close[0]` to determine if the stock hit the limit. In backtesting, `next()` is called at each bar, and `close[0]` is the current bar's closing price. \n\nThe correct approach for a realistic simulation would be:\n- Use `high[0]` for limit up detection (did the stock reach limit up today?)\n- Use `low[0]` for limit down detection (did the stock reach limit down today?)\n\nThis way, if `high[0] >= limit_up[0]`, the stock hit limit up and we shouldn't buy. And if `low[0] <= limit_down[0]`, the stock hit limit down and we shouldn't sell.\n\n\nThe audit flagged this because using `close[0]` means we're checking whether the bar closed at the limit, which is too late—once it closes at limit up, it's already locked and we can't execute. By then it's already too late to place an order anyway, so I need to detect the limit hit during the bar using the high and low prices instead.\n\nThe fix is to check `high[0] >= limit_up` to catch limit-up hits that would lock the stock, and `low[0] <= limit_down` to catch limit-down hits. This way we're simulating what would actually happen intraday when the stock hits its circuit breaker.","thinkingSignature":"71dc68cafbd5bbd3b4c7e3ea709d3f7953d6fc06d01056f46f12ae6b171f45f4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2r0zxg15tr88_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/backtest/run_backtest.py","edits":[{"oldText":"    def _is_limit_up(self):\n        return float(self.data.close[0]) >= float(self.data.limit_up[0]) - 1e-8\n\n    def _is_limit_down(self):\n        return float(self.data.close[0]) <= float(self.data.limit_down[0]) + 1e-8","newText":"    def _is_limit_up(self):\n        # Use high[0] (intraday peak) instead of close[0] to detect limit-up hit\n        # as the stock locks at limit-up the moment high reaches it\n        return float(self.data.high[0]) >= float(self.data.limit_up[0]) - 1e-8\n\n    def _is_limit_down(self):\n        # Use low[0] (intraday trough) instead of close[0] to detect limit-down hit\n        return float(self.data.low[0]) <= float(self.data.limit_down[0]) + 1e-8"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed","usage":{"input":89752,"output":571,"cacheRead":19971,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110294,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775578366981,"responseId":"06245fff2c0480650358dc2f4c35af0d"}}
