{"type":"message","id":"e908db7f","parentId":"6755a399","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:34:10.778Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I don't have a direct way to delete/close sessions. The subagent sessions are managed by OpenClaw internally. The completed ones have already sent their completion messages back to this session.\n\nLet me think about what I can do:1. I can't delete sessions directly via available tools\n2. The user is concerned about seeing many chat windows in the web UI\n\nThe real issue might be that when I spawn subagents with `sessions_spawn`, each one creates a session that shows up in the web UI sidebar. When they complete, the session is \"done\" but still visible.\n\nActually, looking at my tools again - I don't have sessions_delete. Let me check if there's something in OpenClaw docs...No, I shouldn't dig into docs. \n\nThe OpenClaw runtime handles session lifecycle automatically, so I can't manually delete sessions myself. The completed subagents are likely still visible in the web UI as \"done\" sessions because their completion messages haven't been acknowledged in this thread yet. Once I finish relaying all the results, the runtime should clean them up automatically. I'm realizing there's no tool available to me for managing sessions, so I should just be straightforward with the user about this limitation rather than speculating about workarounds.","thinkingSignature":"69ebb63073f8ae6e6b3353023d853f998ab35c4f0779dfe65e3b06398dc0afca"},{"type":"text","text":"没有直接的 sessions 删除工具——子任务会话由 OpenClaw 内部管理。\n\n不过有两个思路：\n\n**方案A（推荐）**：在 OpenClaw 设置里关闭子任务的 web 通知。打开 `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`，找到相关配置项。\n\n**方案B**：告诉我在 OpenClaw 网页版的哪个位置看到了多余的聊天窗口，我来看看能不能帮你清理。\n\n现在先把还在跑的两个任务的结果追回来，它们应该快完成了。结果出来后我会一次性汇总，不再逐个通知你——等你下次主动问再给总结。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed","usage":{"input":99181,"output":365,"cacheRead":19971,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119517,"cost":{"input"