{"type":"message","id":"fded9325","parentId":"aadcb27b","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:52:55.559Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mfnlsifdoxgs_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"            risk_off = True\n            reasons.append(self._fmt_threshold_trigger(\"strategy_max_drawdown_pct\", max_dd, max_dd_th, \">=\"))\n\n        sharpe = context.strategy_sharpe\n        sharpe_th = self.config.strategy_sharpe_cautious_threshold\n        if sharpe_th is not None and sharpe is not None and sharpe < sharpe_th:\n            soft_cautious = True\n            reasons.append(self._fmt_threshold_trigger(\"strategy_sharpe\", sharpe, sharpe_th, \"<\"))\n\n        if hard_stop:\n            risk_off = True\n            mode = \"halt\"\n            halt_new_buy = True\n        elif risk_off:\n            mode = \"cautious\"\n            halt_new_buy = not self.config.allow_new_buy_when_riskoff\n        elif soft_cautious:\n            mode = \"cautious\"\n            halt_new_buy = False\n        else:\n            mode = \"normal\"\n            halt_new_buy = False\n\n        return RiskDecision(\n            mode=mode,\n            risk_off=risk_off,\n            hard_stop=hard_stop,\n            halt_new_buy=halt_new_buy,\n            reason=reasons[0] if reasons else \"\",\n            reasons=reasons,\n        )\n\n    def _apply_weight_caps(self, df: pd.DataFrame, *, exposure_cap: float) -> pd.DataFrame:\n        if \"target_weight\" not in df.columns:\n            return df\n\n        buy_mask = df[\"signal_type\"].isin(self.BUY_SIGNAL_TYPES)\n        approved_buy_mask = buy_mask & df[\"approved\"].fillna(False)\n\n        if not bool(approved_buy_mask.any()):\n            return df\n\n        df[\"target_weight\"] = pd.to_numeric(df[\"target_weight\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n        df.loc[approved_buy_mask, \"target_weight\"] = (\n            df.loc[approved_buy_mask, \"target_weight\"].fillna(0.0).clip(lower=0.0)\n        )\n\n        single_cap_mask = approved_buy_mask & (df[\"target_weight\"] > self.config.max_single_weight)\n        if bool(single_cap_mask.any()):\n            df.loc[single_cap_mask, \"target_weight\"] = self.config.max_single_weight\n\n[228 more lines in file. Use offset=310 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775580775547}}
{"type":"message","id":"064fbcc5","parentId":"fded9325","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:53:11.109Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the bug in `_apply_weight_caps`:\n\n```python\ndf[\"target_weight\"] = pd.to_numeric(df[\"target_weight\"], errors=\"coerce\")\ndf.loc[approved_buy_mask, \"target_weight\"] = (\n    df.loc[approved_buy_mask, \"target_weight\"].fillna(0.0).clip(lower=0.0)\n)\n```\n\nThis converts `target_weight` to numeric, coercing errors to NaN. But then it does:\n```python\nsingle_cap_mask = approved_buy_mask & (df[\"target_weight\"] > self.config.max_single_weight)\n\n\n```\n\nThis comparison with NaN is False for all rows. Then the function continues to scale the approved BUY weights by exposure cap, but 000003.SZ (SELL) never gets modified since it's not in the approved buy mask. So where is 000003.SZ disappearing to? I need to look at the actual `apply()` method to trace the flow. I think the issue might be upstream in how the DataFrame is being constructed or filtered before it reaches this function.\n\nLooking at the risk_off case handling, the logic sets `approved = False` for BUY signals when not allowed, but SELL signals should get `approved = True`. The early return happens before `_apply_weight_caps` is called, so if risk_off is triggered, that function never runs. In the normal case, `_apply_weight_caps` should apply scaling to BUY signals while leaving SELL signals untouched, but then there's an `_apply_liquidity_filter` call that I need to check.\n\n```\nActually, wait - the `_apply_liquidity_filter` only applies to BUY signals, so SELL signals should pass through. And `apply_execution_filter` is called after that, which should reject SELL signals if they hit the limit down. But the result only has 2 rows with BUY signals, and the SELL signal disappeared entirely. Let me trace through `_apply_execution_filter` more carefully - specifically how the market data dictionary is being converted into a DataFrame and merged with the signals.\n```\n\npython\nmd_df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(market_data, orient=\"index\")\n```\n\nThis creates a DataFrame with the market_data keys as the index. Then the columns get renamed and the index is preserved as the `ts_code` column. When this gets merged with the signals DataFrame on `ts_code`, the merge should work correctly as long as the `ts_code` values match between both DataFrames.\n\nBut I'm realizing the real issue might be upstream - let me trace through `_apply_weight_caps` again to see where the row is actually being dropped. I see the issue now—when I call `apply(signals, context.market_data)`, the signals DataFrame gets passed through the pipeline and mutated at each step, but I need to trace exactly where the filtering is happening to understand why 000003.SZ disappears.","thinkingSignature":"aa720262b8367156c249388f09cc476c928ffacb1ceb3180f74e618f8b23115b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cyz0uc08e8zk_1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":80,"offset":330,"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/risk/risk_engine.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed","usage":{"input":117589,"output":668,"cacheRead":19793,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":138050,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775580775563,"responseId":"06246967a7b18a8a8300554660febaaa"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c0038fe9","parentId":"064fbcc5","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:53:11.163Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cyz0uc08e8zk_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        \"\"\"\n        if signals is None or signals.empty:\n            return pd.DataFrame()\n\n        df = signals.copy()\n        if \"signal_type\" not in df.columns:\n            raise ValueError(\"signals 缺少 signal_type 列\")\n        if \"trade_date\" not in df.columns:\n            df[\"trade_date\"] = context.trade_date\n\n        df[\"signal_type\"] = df[\"signal_type\"].astype(str).str.upper().str.strip()\n        df[\"risk_adjustment\"] = \"none\"\n\n        # 0b) 剔除退市/ST股（解决幸存者偏差）\n        if self.config.add_delisted_stocks:\n            from risk.rules.delisted_filter import DelistedFilter\n\n            _delist_filter = DelistedFilter()\n            blocked = _delist_filter.blocked_codes_for_date(context.trade_date)\n            if blocked:\n                blocked_set = set(blocked)\n                removed_mask = df[\"ts_code\"].isin(blocked_set)\n                if removed_mask.any():\n                    _append_audit(\n                        context.trade_date,\n                        \";\".join(df.loc[removed_mask, \"ts_code\"].tolist()),\n                        \"BUY\",\n                        \"BLOCKED_DELISTED_ST\",\n                        f\"delisted_st_filter:{len(blocked)} codes blocked\",\n                    )\n                df = df[~removed_mask].copy()\n\n        if df.empty:\n            return df\n\n        # 1) 剔除黑名单\n        if self.config.blocked_codes:\n            df = df[~df[\"ts_code\"].isin(self.config.blocked_codes)].copy()\n\n        if df.empty:\n            return df\n\n        decision = self.evaluate_runtime_state(context)\n\n        # 2) 风险关闭 / 硬停止\n        if decision.hard_stop:\n            df[\"risk_status\"] = \"blocked\"\n            df[\"risk_adjustment\"] = \"hard_stop\"\n            df[\"approved\"] = False\n            if \"target_weight\" in df.columns:\n                df[\"target_weight\"] = 0.0\n            return df\n\n        if decision.risk_off:\n            df[\"risk_status\"] = \"riskoff\"\n            df[\"approved\"] = df[\"signal_type\"].isin(self.SELL_SIGNAL_TYPES)\n            buy_mask = df[\"signal_type\"].isin(self.BUY_SIGNAL_TYPES)\n            if self.config.allow_new_buy_when_riskoff:\n                df.loc[buy_mask, \"approved\"] = True\n                self._append_adjustment(df, buy_mask, \"riskoff_buy_limited\")\n            else:\n                df.loc[buy_mask, \"approved\"] = False\n                self._append_adjustment(df, buy_mask, \"riskoff_block_buy\")\n                if \"target_weight\" in df.columns:\n                    df.loc[buy_mask, \"target_weight\"] = 0.0\n\n            return self._apply_weight_caps(df, exposure_cap=self.config.riskoff_total_exposure)\n\n        # 3) 正常态：先标记通过，后续补充细化约束\n        df[\"risk_status\"] = \"normal\"\n        df[\"approved\"] = True\n        df = self._apply_weight_caps(df, exposure_cap=self.config.max_total_exposure)\n\n        # 5) 流动性约束\n        df = self._apply_liquidity_filter(df, context.market_data, context.trade_date)\n\n        # 6) 成交模拟过滤（涨跌停/停牌）\n        df = self.apply_execution_filter(df, context.market_data, context.trade_date)\n\n        return df\n\n[128 more lines in file. Use offset=410 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775580791157}}
