{"type":"message","id":"ea2c278e","parentId":"0957294c","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:54:01.621Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"000003.SZ IS in the blocked list! That's why it gets filtered out. The delisted stocks data includes many real stocks. This is actually expected behavior - 000003.SZ is a real delisted stock in the Chinese market. The test data I used happens to use a real delisted stock.\n\nThis is actually correct behavior of the system! The delisted filter is working correctly - it's filtering out stocks that have been delisted. The test data happens to use a delisted stock (000003.SZ).\n\nSo the bug was in my test data, not in the code. The `apply_execution_filter` and the index reset are working correctly. \n\nNow I need to rerun the verification with stocks that are actually still trading to confirm everything's functioning as expected.","thinkingSignature":"a025060b1e460a3514116746da26b88e0d6b10dfe1a6d1d6a295b2a14c5d8738"},{"type":"text","text":"`000003.SZ` 真的是退市股，被正确过滤了。换个活跃股票重测：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1j23cexeuu0i_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && python3 -c \"\nfrom risk.risk_engine import RiskEngine, RiskContext\nimport pandas as pd\n\nengine = RiskEngine()\nsignals = pd.DataFrame({\n    'ts_code': ['000001.SZ', '000002.SZ', '000006.SZ'],  # 改用活跃股\n    'signal_type': ['BUY', 'BUY', 'SELL'],\n    'trade_date': ['20260301', '20260301', '20260301'],\n    'score': [0.8, 0.7, 0.6],\n    'approved': [True, True, True],\n    'risk_adjustment': ['none', 'none', 'none'],\n})\n\nmarket_data = {\n    '000001.SZ': {'ts_code': '000001.SZ', 'trade_date': 20260301, 'open': 10.0, 'high': 11.0, 'low': 9.5, 'close': 11.0, 'limit_up': 10.0, 'limit_down': 9.0, 'suspended': False, 'adv20': 1000000},\n    '000002.SZ': {'ts_code': '000002.SZ', 'trade_date': 20260301, 'open': 10.0, 'high': 10.5, 'low': 9.5, 'close': 10.0, 'limit_u